cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper focuses on face editing using generative adversarial networks (GANs) and specifically addresses issues related to texture, facial attributes, and expression synthesis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel approach to disentangle texture from the original image, which involves training a GAN, making it likely to fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with image synthesis and manipulation. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
